output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of Physics and astronomy, one year after graduation, Professional, scientific and technical activities was the most common industry for White, Asian and Mixed ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities and Information and communication were the most common industries for Black ethnicity graduates, and Information and communication was the most common industry for Other and Not known ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in proportions was Information and communication where Other ethnicity graduates had the highest proportion and Mixed ethnicity graduates had the lowest proportion. The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Financial and insurance activities where Asian ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£42,700) and White ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£31,400). The group with the highest earnings was Asian ethnicity graduates who worked in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of £42,700).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of Physics and astronomy by ethnicity, one year after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2018/19 tax year.
